Files contents and how to use -- Hardware part

1. RTL

Contents: VHDL entities

2. TBENCH

Contents:- VHDL testbenches
	 - get_data.m : matlab script to generate the data for GRU layer (fcgru_fsmd_tb.vhd).
	 - compare_data.m : matlab script to run after modelsim simulation of the GRU layer DUV with its VHDL testbench.
			    Plots relative and absolute error from software generated data and hardware generated data (data_in.txt, data_out.txt)
	 - data_in.txt: contains data generated by get_data.m (in binary vectors format)
	 - data_in_decimal.txt: contains same data in decimal base.
	 - data_out.txt: contains data from sampled outputs of the GRU layer's DUV in binary vector format

3. MODELSIM

Contents:- project .mpf files for the RTL simulations
	 - .do files for the format of the waveforms in modelsim (automatically displays signals selected at first project run)

4. SYNTHESIS

Contents:- .tcl scripts for the synthesis of the entities.
	  To be run in Synopsis design vision with command source /PATH/file.tcl 
	  Outputs the synthesis reports in timing, area, resources in RPT folder


HOW TO USE THE MATLAB TESTBENCH FOR GRU LAYER TESTING.

1. open matlab, tune generic parameters: NBITS, NB_FRAC, NB_INT, NBSAMPLES, OUTPUTS, INPUTS and change format line : '%.XXXs' to --> '%.NBITSs' with the value of NBITS.
2. Open any text editor and tune the generic parameters in the VHDL testbench (same as in the matlab script)
3. open modelsim, open project file (fcgru_fsmd.mpf) run 'compile all' command, double click on simulation configuration, and 'run -all'.
4. in matlab, run compare_data.m (having tuned the generic parameters once again like in the other files)
